<section xml:id="notes-week-02">
  <title>Week 2:  January 19</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      Last week we introduced the reduced row echelon form of a matrix
      and developed an algorithm called Gaussian elimination that
      transformed a matrix into its reduced row echelon form.  In
      our meetings this week, we will explore the significance of the
      reduced row echelon form, find a way to automate Gaussian
      elimination, and recast these questions into a new algebraic
      operation.
    </p>
  </introduction>

